title: Eight inequivalent definitions of finite set

blocks.name: sornom
blocks.content: The range of a single-step monotone function from ` _om ` into a partially ordered set is a chain. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 3-Nov-2014.)
blocks.origin:

df-fin1a
blocks.content: A set is Ia-finite iff it is not the union of two I-infinite sets. Equivalent to definition Ia of [Levy58] p. 2. A I-infinite Ia-finite set is also known as an amorphous set. This is the second of Levy's eight definitions of finite set. Levy's I-finite is equivalent to our ~ df-fin and not repeated here. These eight definitions are equivalent with Choice but strictly decreasing in strength in models where Choice fails; conversely, they provide a series of increasingly stronger notions of infiniteness. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin2
blocks.content: A set is II-finite (Tarski finite) iff every nonempty chain of subsets contains a maximum element. Definition II of [Levy58] p. 2. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin4
blocks.content: A set is IV-finite (Dedekind finite) iff it has no equinumerous proper subset. Definition IV of [Levy58] p. 3. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin3
blocks.content: A set is III-finite (weakly Dedekind finite) iff its power set is Dedekind finite. Definition III of [Levy58] p. 2. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin5
blocks.content: A set is V-finite iff it behaves finitely under ` +c ` . Definition V of [Levy58] p. 3. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin6
blocks.content: A set is VI-finite iff it behaves finitely under ` X. ` . Definition VI of [Levy58] p. 4. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

blocks.name: df-fin7
blocks.content: A set is VII-finite iff it cannot be infinitely well-ordered. Equivalent to definition VII of [Levy58] p. 4. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 12-Nov-2014.)

thm infpssrlem5(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  ⊢ (w0 →(c0 ∈ c1 → _om[≼]c0))
  ⊣ (w0 → c2 ⊆ c0)
  ⊣ (w0 →(c3 : c2 ↔ c0))
  ⊣ (w0 → c4 ∈(c0 \ c2))
  ⊣ c5 =(rec(`' c3, c4)|` _om)
} = {
  syl5com(w0, c0 ∈ c1, _om[≼]c0, (c5 : _om ↣ c0))
  sylanbrc(w0, (c5 : _om ↣ c0), (c5 : _om → c0), ∀(hs0 ∈ _om, ∀(hs1 ∈ _om,((c5 ` hs0)=(c5 ` hs1)→ hs0 = hs1))))
  infpssrlem3(c5, c0, c2, c3, c4, w0)
  ralrimivva(hs0, hs1, com, com, w0, ((c5 ` hs0)=(c5 ` hs1)→ hs0 = hs1))
  sylibrd((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), (c5 ` hs0)=(c5 ` hs1), hs0 = hs1, ¬(hs0 ∈ hs1 ∨ hs1 ∈ hs0))
  necon2bd((c5 ` hs0), (c5 ` hs1), (w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), (hs0 ∈ hs1 ∨ hs1 ∈ hs0))
  ex((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), (hs0 ∈ hs1 ∨ hs1 ∈ hs0), (c5 ` hs0)≠(c5 ` hs1))
  jaodan((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), hs0 ∈ hs1, hs1 ∈ hs0, (c5 ` hs0)≠(c5 ` hs1))
  necomd((c5 ` hs0), (c5 ` hs1), ((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om))∧ hs0 ∈ hs1))
  syl3anc(((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om))∧ hs0 ∈ hs1), (c5 ` hs1)≠(c5 ` hs0), w0, hs1 ∈ _om, hs0 ∈ hs1)
  simpll(w0, (hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om), hs0 ∈ hs1)
  simplrr(w0, hs0 ∈ _om, hs1 ∈ _om, hs0 ∈ hs1)
  simpr((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), hs0 ∈ hs1)
  infpssrlem4(hs1, hs0, c5, c2, c0, c3, c4, w0)
  syl3anc(((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om))∧ hs1 ∈ hs0), (c5 ` hs0)≠(c5 ` hs1), w0, hs0 ∈ _om, hs1 ∈ hs0)
  simpll(w0, (hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om), hs1 ∈ hs0)
  simplrl(w0, hs0 ∈ _om, hs1 ∈ _om, hs1 ∈ hs0)
  simpr((w0 ∧(hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om)), hs1 ∈ hs0)
  infpssrlem4(hs0, hs1, c5, c2, c0, c3, c4, w0)
  adantl(w0, (hs0 ∈ _om ∧ hs1 ∈ _om), (hs0 = hs1 ↔ ¬(hs0 ∈ hs1 ∨ hs1 ∈ hs0)))
  syl2an(hs0 ∈ _om, hs1 ∈ _om, (hs0 = hs1 ↔ ¬(hs0 ∈ hs1 ∨ hs1 ∈ hs0)), Ord(hs0), Ord(hs1))
  nnord(hs0)
  nnord(hs1)
  ordtri3(hs0, hs1)
  dff13(hs0, hs1, c5, com, c0)
  f1domg(c0, c1, c5, com)
  diff.hs0.s(hs1)
  diff.hs1.c(com)
  diff.hs0.w(w0)
  diff.hs1.w(w0)
  diff.hs0.c(c5)
  diff.hs0.c(com)
  diff.hs1.c(c5)
}

thm infpssr(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1))
} = {
  mpcom(wa(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1), wex(hs0, wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), c0)))))
  adantr(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1), wex(hs0, wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), c0)))))
  pssnel(hs0, c0, c1)
  exlimiv(hs0, wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), c0))), wi(wa(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1)))
  sylbir(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), c0))), wi(wa(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1)), wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)))
  eldif(cv(hs0), c1, c0)
  impd(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1))
  syl5(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wpss(c0, c1), wi(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1)), wss(c0, c1))
  pssss(c0, c1)
  ex(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1), wi(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1)))
  syl5bi(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1), wex(hs1, wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1)))
  bren(hs1, c0, c1)
  exlimdv(hs1, wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1))
  ex(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1), wbr(com, cdom, c1))
  mpd(wa(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1), wcel(c1, universe))
  syl6eqelr(c1, universe, crn(cv(hs1)), wa(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1)))
  3syl(wa(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1)), wceq(crn(cv(hs1)), c1), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1), wfo(cv(hs1), c0, c1))
  f1ofo(cv(hs1), c0, c1)
  forn(cv(hs1), c0, c1)
  rnex(cv(hs1))
  vex(hs1)
  infpssrlem5(c1, universe, c0, cv(hs1), cv(hs0), cres(crdg(ccnv(cv(hs1)), cv(hs0)), com), wa(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1)))
  simplr(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1))
  simpr(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1))
  simpll(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1), wf1o(cv(hs1), c0, c1))
  eqid(cres(crdg(ccnv(cv(hs1)), cv(hs0)), com))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(wi(wa(wpss(c0, c1), wbr(c0, cen, c1)), wbr(com, cdom, c1)))
  diff.hs1.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.c(c1)
  diff.hs1.w(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c0)), wss(c0, c1)))
  diff.hs1.w(wbr(com, cdom, c1))
}

  sylbir((hs0 ∈ c1 ∧ ¬ hs0 ∈ c0), ((c0 ⊊ c1 ∧ c0[≅]c1)→ _om[≼]c1), hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0))
  eldif(hs0, c1, c0)
  impd(hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0), c0 ⊊ c1, c0[≅]c1, _om[≼]c1)
  syl5(hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0), c0 ⊊ c1, (c0[≅]c1 → _om[≼]c1), c0 ⊆ c1)
  pssss(c0, c1)

  syl5bi((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1), c0[≅]c1, _om[≼]c1, ∃(hs1,(hs1 : c0 ↔ c1)))
  bren(hs1, c0, c1)
  exlimdv(hs1, (hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1), (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1), _om[≼]c1)
  ex((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1), (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1), _om[≼]c1)
  mpd(((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1)∧(hs1 : c0 ↔ c1)), _om[≼]c1, c1 ∈ 𝕌)
  syl6eqelr(c1, universe, ran(hs1), ((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1)∧(hs1 : c0 ↔ c1)))
  3syl(((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1)∧(hs1 : c0 ↔ c1)), ran(hs1)= c1, (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1), (hs1 : c0 ↠ c1))
  f1ofo(hs1, c0, c1)

  infpssrlem5(c1, universe, c0, hs1, hs0, (rec(`' hs1, hs0)|` _om), ((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1)∧(hs1 : c0 ↔ c1)))
  simplr(hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0), c0 ⊆ c1, (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1))
  simpr((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1), (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1))
  simpll(hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0), c0 ⊆ c1, (hs1 : c0 ↔ c1))
  eqid((rec(`' hs1, hs0)|` _om))

  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(((c0 ⊊ c1 ∧ c0[≅]c1)→ _om[≼]c1))
  diff.hs1.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.c(c1)
  diff.hs1.w((hs0 ∈(c1 \ c0)∧ c0 ⊆ c1))
  diff.hs1.w(_om[≼]c1)
}

  exlimdv(hs0, wf1o(cv(hs1), c1, c0), wa(wpss(cv(hs0), c1), wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c1)), wn(wcel(c0, cfin4)))
  ex(wf1o(cv(hs1), c1, c0), wa(wpss(cv(hs0), c1), wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c1)), wn(wcel(c0, cfin4)))
  syl2anc(wa(wf1o(cv(hs1), c1, c0), wa(wpss(cv(hs0), c1), wbr(cv(hs0), cen, c1))), wn(wcel(c0, cfin4)), wpss(cima(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)), c0), wbr(cima(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)), cen, c0))

  jctir(wpss(cv(hs0), c1), wss(cv(hs0), c1), wss(c1, c1))
  ssid(c1)

  adantr(wf1o(cv(hs1), c1, c0), wpss(cv(hs0), c1), wceq(cima(cv(hs1), c1), c0))
  3eqtr3a(cima(cv(hs1), c1), c0, cima(cv(hs1), cdm(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)), wf1o(cv(hs1), c1, c0))
  imadmrn(cv(hs1))

} = {

  bren(hs1, c1, c0)
  exlimiv(hs1, (hs1 : c1 ↔ c0), (c0 ∈ Fin4 → ¬ ∃(hs0,(hs0 ⊊ c1 ∧ hs0[≅]c1))))

blocks.name: fin23lem34
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ fin23 . Establish induction invariants on ` Y ` which parameterizes our contradictory chain of subsets. In this section, ` h ` is the hypothetically assumed family of subsets, ` g ` is the ground set, and ` i ` is the induction function constructed in the previous section. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 2-Nov-2014.)

thm isf32lem12(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, c1), wi(wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(c0, c2)))
  -| wceq(c2, cab(s0, wral(s1, co(cpw(cv(s0)), cmap, com), wi(wral(s2, com, wss(cfv(cv(s1), csuc(cv(s2))), cfv(cv(s1), cv(s2)))), wcel(cint(crn(cv(s1))), crn(cv(s1)))))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
} = {
  a1ii(wi(wcel(c0, c1), wi(wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(c0, c2))), diffsc(s0, c2))
  sylibrd(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(c0, c2), wral(hs1, co(cpw(c0), cmap, com), wi(wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1))))))
  ralrimdv(hs1, co(cpw(c0), cmap, com), wcel(c0, c1), wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wi(wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)))))
  com4t(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(cv(hs1), co(cpw(c0), cmap, com)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1))))
  syl(wcel(cv(hs1), co(cpw(c0), cmap, com)), wi(wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wi(wcel(c0, c1), wi(wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)))))), wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)))
  elmapi(cv(hs1), cpw(c0), com)
  exp31(wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wcel(c0, c1), wi(wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)))))
  con1d(wa(wa(wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0))))), wcel(c0, c1)), wbr(com, cwdom, c0), wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1))))
  impancom(wa(wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0))))), wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)))), wbr(com, cwdom, c0))
  3expa(wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wn(wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1)))), wi(wcel(c0, c1), wbr(com, cwdom, c0)))
  expcom(w3a(wf(cv(hs1), com, cpw(c0)), wral(hs0, com, wss(cfv(cv(hs1), csuc(cv(hs0))), cfv(cv(hs1), cv(hs0)))), wn(wcel(cint(crn(cv(hs1))), crn(cv(hs1))))), wcel(c0, c1), wbr(com, cwdom, c0))
  isf32lem11(hs0, c0, c1, cv(hs1))
  isfin3ds(hs1, hs0, s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2)
  diff.hs1.w(wcel(c0, c1))
  diff.hs1.w(wn(wbr(com, cwdom, c0)))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(cv(hs1))
  diff.hs1.s(hs0)
  diff.hs1.s(s0)
  diff.hs1.s(s1)
  diff.hs1.s(s2)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.s(s2)

  ⊣ d(s1, c0)
  ⊣ d(s2, c0)
} = {
  a1ii((c0 ∈ c1 →(¬ _om[≼*]c0 → c0 ∈ c2)), d(s0, c2))
  sylibrd(c0 ∈ c1, ¬ _om[≼*]c0, c0 ∈ c2, ∀(hs1 ∈(P(c0)[↦]_om),(∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0))→ ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1))))

  com4t(c0 ∈ c1, ¬ _om[≼*]c0, hs1 ∈(P(c0)[↦]_om), ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0)), ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1))
  syl(hs1 ∈(P(c0)[↦]_om), (∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0))→(c0 ∈ c1 →(¬ _om[≼*]c0 → ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1)))), (hs1 : _om → P(c0)))
  elmapi(hs1, P(c0), com)
  exp31((hs1 : _om → P(c0)), ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0)), c0 ∈ c1, (¬ _om[≼*]c0 → ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1)))
  con1d((((hs1 : _om → P(c0))∧ ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0)))∧ c0 ∈ c1), _om[≼*]c0, ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1))
  impancom(((hs1 : _om → P(c0))∧ ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0))), c0 ∈ c1, ¬ ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1), _om[≼*]c0)
  3expa((hs1 : _om → P(c0)), ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0)), ¬ ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1), (c0 ∈ c1 → _om[≼*]c0))
  expcom(((hs1 : _om → P(c0))∧ ∀(hs0 ∈ _om,(hs1 ` suc(hs0))⊆(hs1 ` hs0))∧ ¬ ⋂ ran(hs1)∈ ran(hs1)), c0 ∈ c1, _om[≼*]c0)
  isf32lem11(hs0, c0, c1, hs1)
  isfin3ds(hs1, hs0, s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2)
  diff.hs1.w(c0 ∈ c1)
  diff.hs1.w(¬ _om[≼*]c0)

  diff.hs1.s(s0)
  diff.hs1.s(s1)
  diff.hs1.s(s2)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.s(s2)

}

blocks.name: fin23
blocks.content: Every II-finite set (every chain of subsets has a maximal element) is III-finite (has no denumerable collection of subsets). The proof here is the only one I could find, from ~ http://matwbn.icm.edu.pl/ksiazki/fm/fm6/fm619.pdf p.94 (writeup by Tarski, credited to Kuratowski). Translated into English and modern notation, the proof proceeds as follows (variables renamed for uniqueness): Suppose for a contradiction that ` A ` is a set which is II-finite but not III-finite. For any countable sequence of distinct subsets ` T ` of ` A ` , we can form a decreasing sequence of nonempty subsets ` ( U `` T ) ` by taking finite intersections of initial segments of ` T ` while skipping over any element of ` T ` which would cause the intersection to be empty. By II-finiteness (as ~ fin2i2 ) this sequence contains its intersection, call it ` Y ` ; since by induction every subset in the sequence ` U ` is nonempty, the intersection must be nonempty. Suppose that an element ` X ` of ` T ` has nonempty intersection with ` Y ` . Thus, said element has a nonempty intersection with the corresponding element of ` U ` , therefore it was used in the construction of ` U ` and all further elements of ` U ` are subsets of ` X ` , thus ` X ` contains the ` Y ` . That is, all elements of ` X ` either contain ` Y ` or are disjoint from it. Since there are only two cases, there must exist an infinite subset of ` T ` which uniformly either contain ` Y ` or are disjoint from it. In the former case we can create an infinite set by subtracting ` Y ` from each element. In either case, call the result ` Z ` ; this is an infinite set of subsets of ` A ` , each of which is disjoint from ` Y ` and contained in the union of ` T ` ; the union of ` Z ` is strictly contained in the union of ` T ` , because only the latter is a superset of the nonempty set ` Y ` . The preceding four steps may be iterated a countable number of times starting from the assumed denumerable set of subsets to produce a denumerable sequence ` B ` of the ` T ` sets from each stage. Great caution is required to avoid ~ ax-dc here; in particular an effective version of the pigeonhole principle (for aleph-null pigeons and 2 holes) is required. Since a denumerable set of subsets is assumed to exist, we can conclude ` _om e. _V ` without the axiom. This ` B ` sequence is strictly decreasing, thus it has no minimum, contradicting the first assumption. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 2-Nov-2014.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 17-May-2015.)

blocks.content: Every Ia-finite set is II-finite. Theorem 1 of [Levy58], p. 3. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 8-Nov-2014.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 17-May-2015.)

thm fin1a2(class c0) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, cfin1a), wcel(c0, cfin2))
} = {
  mpdan(wcel(c0, cfin1a), wcel(c0, cfin2), wral(hs0, cpw(c0), wo(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfin2))))
  ralrimiva(hs0, cpw(c0), wcel(c0, cfin1a), wo(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfin2)))
  sylan2(wcel(c0, cfin1a), wcel(cv(hs0), cpw(c0)), wo(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfin2)), wss(cv(hs0), c0))
  elpwi(cv(hs0), c0)
  syl(wa(wcel(c0, cfin1a), wss(cv(hs0), c0)), wo(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfin2)), wo(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfn)))
  fin1ai(c0, cv(hs0))
  orim2i(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfn), wcel(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)), cfin2))
  fin12(cdif(c0, cv(hs0)))
  fin1a2s(hs0, c0, cfin1a)
  diff.hs0.w(wcel(c0, cfin1a))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(cfin1a)
}

thm fin1a2(class c0) {
  ⊢ (c0 ∈ Fin1a → c0 ∈ Fin2)
} = {
  mpdan(c0 ∈ Fin1a, c0 ∈ Fin2, ∀(hs0 ∈ P(c0),(hs0 ∈ Fin ∨(c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin2)))
  ralrimiva(hs0, P(c0), c0 ∈ Fin1a, (hs0 ∈ Fin ∨(c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin2))
  sylan2(c0 ∈ Fin1a, hs0 ∈ P(c0), (hs0 ∈ Fin ∨(c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin2), hs0 ⊆ c0)
  elpwi(hs0, c0)
  syl((c0 ∈ Fin1a ∧ hs0 ⊆ c0), (hs0 ∈ Fin ∨(c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin2), (hs0 ∈ Fin ∨(c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin))
  fin1ai(c0, hs0)
  orim2i(hs0 ∈ Fin, (c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin, (c0 \ hs0)∈ Fin2)
  fin12((c0 \ hs0))
  fin1a2s(hs0, c0, cfin1a)
  diff.hs0.w(c0 ∈ Fin1a)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(cfin1a)
}
